security items in hand luggage. international passengers should be prepared for scrutiny of their baggage, including all carry-on items. when departing, you will likely pass through a total of three security checkpoints, and possibly a further one at the boarding gate, so be patient, particularly when things are busy. security protocols at the domestic terminal are similar to those applied at other indonesian domestic hub airports, with baggage and carry-on screening, x-ray, metal detection, hand inspections and other security measures in place for departing passengers. be mindful of airport porters who may attempt to take control of your luggage either 